The antidote animadverted, by P. Prynne, William, 1600-1669.
8 p.
s.n., [London : 1645]
P. = William Prynne. Caption title. Imprint from Wing; foot of page 8, above "Finis", reads: Printed according to order. A reply to "An antidote against foure dangerous quæries" (Wing A3493), which was a reply to Prynne's "Foure serious questions of grand importance" (Wing P3959). Annotation on Thomason copy: "Septemb: 17th 1645". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
